    <etym xml:lang="ru">Разлагаем %ifī-d-%i ← %i*pati-dā%i буквально „давать взамен“, „возмещать“.
        Основа глагола %idā%i ‘давать’ выступает с нулевой огласовкой (как в <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_raddyn"/> ‘дать’), в отличие от %ifī-da-wyn%i ‘мириться’ [см. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_fīdawyn"/>], где имеем сильную ступень; ср. %ist-yn%i [см. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_styn"/>], %iæft-yn%i [см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æftyn"
        />], %ifæz-m-yn%i [см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæzmyn"/>] рядом с %ista-jyn%i [см.
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_stajyn"/>], %iæfta-wyn%i [см. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æftawyn"/>], %iny-ma-jyn%i [см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_nymajyn"
        />]. По образованию и значению ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><lang/><w>prati-dā-</w><gloss><q>давать взамен</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="pal-x-turfan"
                ><lang/><w>patdahišn</w><gloss><q>воздаяние</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>p’črʼt
            (*pati-rāta-)</w><gloss><q>возмещение</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>плата</q></gloss></mentioned>, . В ряде восточноиранских языков
        находим сочетание %i*para-dā%i со значением ‘продавать’: <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><lang/><w>pr’δ-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"
            ><lang/><w>parδāδ-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"
            ><lang/><w>parδē</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"
            ><lang/><w>plār-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"
            ><lang/><w>pəlōr-</w></mentioned> и др. (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"
                /><biblScope>II 237</biblScope></bibl>). О корне %ida-%i ‘давать’ см. под <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_dæddyn"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_raddyn"/>. Другие
        этимологические опыты см.: <bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Н. Petersson. Etymologische
                Miszellen. LUA XIX 5 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Н. Petersson.
                Etymologische Miszellen. LUA XIX 5 ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Sköld._Oss."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">XX 20 сл.</biblScope><biblScope
                xml:lang="en">XX 20 ff.</biblScope></bibl> %bВенг.%b <mentioned xml:lang="hu"
                ><lang/><w>fizet-, füzet-</w><gloss><q>платить</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="hu"><w/><gloss><q>возмещать</q></gloss></mentioned>, считается усвоенным из
        аланского; ос. %ifid-%i → венг. %ifiz-%i, как <ref type="xr" target="#entry_būd"/> →
        %ibüz%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qæd"/> → %igaz%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ad"/>
        → %iéz%i (<bibl><author>Munkácsi</author><ref target="#ref_KSz."/><biblScope>V
                317</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Sköld._Oss."/><biblScope
                xml:lang="ru">20 сл., 55</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">20 ff.,
            55</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
            /><biblScope>251</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">The word is divided %ifī-d-%i ← %i*pati-dā%i literally ‘give in exchange
        for’, ‘reimburse’. The verb stem %idā%i ‘give’ is with zero-ablaut (as in <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_raddyn"/> ‘give’), as opposed to %ifī-da-wyn%i ‘reconcile’ [see <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_fīdawyn"/>], where there is a strong ablaut grade; cf.
        %ist-yn%i [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_styn"/>], %iæft-yn%i [see <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æftyn"/>], %ifæz-m-yn%i [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæzmyn"/>] and
        %ista-jyn%i [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_stajyn"/>], %iæfta-wyn%i [see <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æftawyn"/>], %iny-ma-jyn%i [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_nymajyn"
        />]. As for the derivation pattern and the meaning, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>prati-dā-</w><gloss><q>give in exchange for</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="pal-x-turfan"
                ><lang/><w>patdahišn</w><gloss><q>retribution</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>p’črʼt
            (*pati-rāta-)</w><gloss><q>reimbursement</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><w/><gloss><q>payment</q></gloss></mentioned>, . There is a combination
        %i*para-dā%i in some East Iranian languages with the meaning ‘sell’: <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>pr’δ-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"
                ><lang/><w>parδāδ-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"
            ><lang/><w>parδē</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"
            ><lang/><w>plār-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"
            ><lang/><w>pəlōr-</w></mentioned> etc. (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"
                /><biblScope>II 237</biblScope></bibl>). About the root %ida-%i ‘give’ see under
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dæddyn"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_raddyn"/>. See
        other etymological experiences: <bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Н. Petersson. Etymologische
                Miszellen. LUA XIX 5 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Н. Petersson.
                Etymologische Miszellen. LUA XIX 5 ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Sköld._Oss."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">XX 20 сл.</biblScope><biblScope
                xml:lang="en">XX 20 ff.</biblScope></bibl>
        <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/><w>fizet-,
            füzet-</w><gloss><q>pay</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="hu"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>reimburse</q></gloss></mentioned>, is considered to be acquired
        from Alan; Ossetic %ifid-%i → Hungarian %ifiz-%i, as <ref type="xr" target="#entry_būd"/> →
        %ibüz%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qæd"/> → %igaz%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ad"/>
        → %iéz%i (<bibl><author>Munkácsi</author><ref target="#ref_KSz."/><biblScope>V
                317</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Sköld._Oss."/><biblScope
                xml:lang="ru">20 сл., 55</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">20 ff.,
            55</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
            /><biblScope>251</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
